data.title: Tracey Ullman at Emmy Awards
data.meta_description: Title supplied by cataloger.Photograph caption dated September 18, 1989 reads, "To Tracey Ullman the Emmys mean 'pizza at Spago...I hope I win this time so I can swallow it.'" "The Tracey Ullman Show" won 4 Emmys: Outstanding Achievement in Choreography, Outstanding Achievement in Makeup for a Series, Outstanding Art Direction for a Variety or Music Program, Outstanding Variety, Music or Comedy Program; the show was also nominated for: Outstanding Achievement in Graphic Design and Title Sequences, Outstanding Achievement in Hairstyling for a Series, Outstanding Directing in a Variety or Music Program, Outstanding Editing for a Series - Multi-Camera Production, Outstanding Individual Performance in a Variety or Music Program, Outstanding Writing in a Variety or Music Program. The 41st Annual Primetime Emmy Awards were held on September 17, 1989 at the Pasadena Civic Auditorium.
